info.document:
Ford Motor Co. and Henderson Ford recently announced they will support students' educational efforts by extending the College Student Purchase Program through Jan. 2.

The program boosts students' finances with car leases and purchases through affordable loan rates, bonus cash and deferred payments. Students are eligible if they are enrolled in a half to full-time accredited four-year college/university, graduate school, junior college, community college or trade school, or are a high school graduate with a letter of intent to attend one of these institutions. Recent graduates within the last three years, college student interns, trade school apprentices and medical students in residency are also qualified if they have attended classes between May 1, 2014 through Jan. 2, 2018.

Eligible vehicles for a $500 program bonus include 2018s Fusion Gas, Flex, Transit Connect; 2017s C-Max Energi, C-Max Hybrid, Fiesta, Focus Electric, Focus Gas, Fusion Energi, Fusion Gas, Fusion Hybrid, Mustang GT, Mustang 14, Mustang V6, Taurus, Edge, Escape, Flex, Explorer, Expedition, F-150 Regular Cab, F-150 Super Crew, F-150 SuperCab, F-Super Duty, E-Series, Transit Connect, Transit; 2016s Focus Electric, Taurus, Edge, F-150 Regular Cab, F-150 SuperCab, F-150 SuperCrew, Transit Connect and Transit.

For information, visit hendersonfamilyford.com.
